name: maria muñoz
text:
Lugar humilde con gente encantadora. Fina y Mari, amor de hermanas! Comida casera sin pretensiones y excelente. La cocinera de diez. La atención de diez. La calidad de once.
El pulpo el mejor que he comido. Las xibias blancas, suaves, sabrosas… la zorza casera y picante como debe ser. Las medias raciones suficientes pero se hacen cortas de lo bueno que está todo. Te invitan a una tapina con la consumición. Especial mención a la salsa casera y picante de Fina. El trato más que amable. No admiten pago con tarjeta, solo efectivo.
Parada obligada si estás en Burela o alrededores.
textTranslated:
A humble place with lovely people. Fina and Mari, sisterly love! Unpretentious, excellent homemade food. The cook is a ten, the service is a ten, the quality is a eleven.
The octopus is the best I've ever eaten. The white xibias are tender and tasty... the homemade zorza is spicy as it should be. The half-portions are sufficient, but they seem small considering how good everything is. They offer you a tapas with your drink. A special mention to Fina's homemade spicy sauce. The service is more than friendly. They don't accept card payments, only cash.
A must-stop if you're in Burela or the surrounding area.

The potatoes were NATURAL, not from bags like some restaurants.
If you want to have lunch/dinner in a family-friendly place where the portions are generous, I recommend this place! And then you have the ocean just 5 minutes away to work off everything you're going to eat.
We'll be back :)
